<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-596-220  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 596 220.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  June 11 1990 n372 p38(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell: sales, income up. (nixed merger try has little effect on2Q financials)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Novell Inc shows no ill-effects from its failed merger with LotusDevelopment Corp, as 2nd qtr 1990 results are on-target withanalyst's predictions.andP;  Novell's net income for the quarterincreased to $20.5 million, up from $11.5 million for the sameperiod a year ago.andP;  Earnings per share for the quarter jumped 71percent to 60 cents, up from 35 cents a share one year ago.andO;Novell's revenue for the 2nd qtr 1990 is $120 million, up from$110.4 million a year ago.andP;  Novell is pleased with the results,stating they show the company is on a steady course of growth.andO;Software sales were responsible for 75 percent of Novell's totalrevenue at the end of the 2nd qtr, up from 72 percent for the 1stqtr.andP;  Gross margins increased from 63 percent for 2nd qtr 1989 to71 percent in the same period in 1990.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (earnings).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Topic:     Second QuarterProfitFinancial Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>